name: Swedish Limpu Bread
author: Ruth Uitto
summary: Light, golden loaf Swedes have served for centuries.
directions: Boil water, sugar, oil, salt, orange rind, caraway seeds, and fennel seeds in a saucepan for 3 minutes
Cool until warm In a large bowl, whisk together 3 cups flour and yeast
Stir in cooled orange rind mixture
Beat with an electric mixer on medium speed for 2 minutes
Blend in eggs
Add 1 cup flour, and beat 1 minute on medium speed
Add rye flour and enough additional white flour to make a stiff dough
Turn dough onto a lightly floured surface
Knead for 8 to 10 minutes, or until smooth and satiny
Shape into a ball
Place in lightly greased bowl, turning to grease  the surface
Cover with a damp cloth, and place in a warm spot
Allow to rise for 1 1/2 hours, or until doubled
Punch dough down, and divide in half
Shape into 2 balls
Let rest for 10 min
Shape into 2  loaves, and place into ungreased 9 x 5 inch loaf pans
Brush with oil
Allow to rise for 1 hour, or until doubled in size
Bake at 400 degrees F (205 degrees C) for 30 to 35 minutes, or until done
